{"title_page": "V\u00e9ronique Renties", "text_new": "{{Infobox Athlete\n |name                       = V\u00e9ronique Renties\n |event                = [[middle distance running]]\n |years_active            = 1978-1980\n |nationality              = [[France|French]]\n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age |3 July 1960}}\n |birth_place         = [[Valenciennes]]\n}}\n\n'''V\u00e9ronique Renties''' (born 3 July 1960 at [[Valenciennes]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialized in the [[Middle-distance running|middle distances]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nShe won five French Championship Athletic titles:   two in  the [[800 meters]] in 1979 and 1980 and three in the [[1500 meters]] in 1978, 1979 and 1980.\n\nShe held the [[:fr:Records de France juniors d'athl\u00e9tisme|French junior record]] for [[:fr:1 000 m\u00e8tres|1000 meters]] in 2:37.2 (1979).\n\n=== Prize list  ===\n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French Championships in Athletics]]   :  \n** 2 times winner 800&nbsp;m in [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1979|1979]] and [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1980|1980]].   \n** 3 times winner of 1,500&nbsp;m in [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1978|1978]],  [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1979|1979]] and [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1980|1980]].\n\n=== Records ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''Personal Bests'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n|-\n|800 m\n|2:04.1\n|\n|1979\n|-\n|1 500 m\n|4:10.54\n|\n|1980\n|}\n\n== Notes and references  ==\n* Docathl\u00e92003, F\u00e9d\u00e9ration fran\u00e7aise d'athl\u00e9tisme, 2003, p.&nbsp;429\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Renties, Veronique}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Valenciennes]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French female middle-distance runners]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games silver medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games medalists in athletics]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 1979 Mediterranean Games]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Athlete\n |name                       = V\u00e9ronique Renties\n |event                = [[middle distance running]]\n |years_active            = 1978-1980\n |nationality              = [[France|French]]\n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age |3 July 1960}}\n |birth_place         = [[Valenciennes]]\n}}\n\n'''V\u00e9ronique Renties''' (born 3 July 1960 at [[Valenciennes]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialized in the [[Middle-distance running|middle distances]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nShe won five French Championship Athletic titles:   two in  the [[800 meters]] in 1979 and 1980 and three in the [[1500 meters]] in 1978, 1979 and 1980.\n\nShe held the [[:fr:Records de France juniors d'athl\u00e9tisme|French junior record]] for [[:fr:1 000 m\u00e8tres|1000 meters]] in 2:37.2 (1979).\n\n=== Prize list  ===\n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French Championships in Athletics]]   :  \n** 2 times winner 800&nbsp;m in [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1979|1979]] and [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1980|1980]].   \n** 3 times winner of 1,500&nbsp;m in [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1978|1978]],  [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1979|1979]] and [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1980|1980]].\n\n=== Records ===\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''Personal Bests'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n|-\n|800 m\n|2:04.1\n|\n|1979\n|-\n|1 500 m\n|4:10.54\n|\n|1980\n|}\n\n== Notes and references  ==\n* Docathl\u00e92003, F\u00e9d\u00e9ration fran\u00e7aise d'athl\u00e9tisme, 2003, p.&nbsp;429\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Renties, Veronique}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Valenciennes]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French female middle-distance runners]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games silver medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games medalists in athletics]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 1979 Mediterranean Games]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "WOSlinker", "label": "safe", "comment": "tidy wikitable options", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V%C3%A9ronique_Renties"}
{"title_page": "Catherine Delachanal", "text_new": "{{Infobox Athlete\n |name                       = Catherine Delachanal\n |discipline                = [[400 m]]\n |nationality               = {{FRA}}\n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age|4 April 1952}}\n |birth_place         = [[Triel-sur-Seine]] \n}}\n\n'''Catherine Delachanal''' (born 4 April [[1952 in sports|1952]] at [[Triel-sur-Seine]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], specialising in the  [[400 metres|400 meters]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nCatherine Delachanal won three French champion titles for the 400 meters, two outdoor in 1977 and 1979, and one indoor in 1977. She twice set the [[:fr:Record de France du relais 4 \u00d7 100 m\u00e8tres|French record for the 4 \u00d7 100 Metres Relay]], running  44.2 in 1974, and 43.8 in 1976.\n\nShe participated in the [[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Olympics]] in Montreal, where she reached the quarterfinals of the [[200 metres|200 meters]] and was eliminated in the qualifying heats of the [[4 \u00d7 100 metres relay|4 \u00d7 100 m]].\n\n===  Prize list  ===\n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French Championships in Athletics]]   :  \n** 2 times winner of the 400m [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1977|1977]] and [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1979|1979]]   \n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme en salle|Indoor Athletics Championships of France]]   :  \n** winner of the 400 m in 1977\n\n=== Records ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''Personal records'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" |Place\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n|-\n|100 m\n|11.5\n|\n|1976\n|-\n|200 m\n|23.0\n|\n|1976\n|-\n|400 m\n|52.8\n|\n|1976\n|}\n\n==  notes and references  ==\n\n{{Empty section|date=January 2016}}\n\n==  External links  ==\n*  Docathl\u00e92003, French Athletics Federation, 2003, p.&nbsp;398   \n*   <span class=\"indicateur-langue\">(<abbr class=\"abbr\" title=\"Langue : anglais\">in</abbr>)</span><span> Olympic profile</span><nowiki>   </nowiki>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/de/catherine-delachanal-1.html Catherine Delachanal]<span> sure </span>'' sports-reference.com''\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Delachanal, Catherine}}\n[[Category:French female sprinters]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of France]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games gold medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games medalists in athletics]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 1975 Mediterranean Games]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Athlete\n |name                       = Catherine Delachanal\n |discipline                = [[400 m]]\n |nationality               = {{FRA}}\n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age|4 April 1952}}\n |birth_place         = [[Triel-sur-Seine]] \n}}\n\n'''Catherine Delachanal''' (born 4 April [[1952 in sports|1952]] at [[Triel-sur-Seine]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], specialising in the  [[400 metres|400 meters]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nCatherine Delachanal won three French champion titles for the 400 meters, two outdoor in 1977 and 1979, and one indoor in 1977. She twice set the [[:fr:Record de France du relais 4 \u00d7 100 m\u00e8tres|French record for the 4 \u00d7 100 Metres Relay]], running  44.2 in 1974, and 43.8 in 1976.\n\nShe participated in the [[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Olympics]] in Montreal, where she reached the quarterfinals of the [[200 metres|200 meters]] and was eliminated in the qualifying heats of the [[4 \u00d7 100 metres relay|4 \u00d7 100 m]].\n\n===  Prize list  ===\n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French Championships in Athletics]]   :  \n** 2 times winner of the 400m [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00