{"title_page": "Sophie Malbranque", "text_new": "{{Infobox Athlete\n |name                       = Sophie Malbranque\n |event                = [[400 m]]\n |nationality               = {{FRA}}\n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age |24 December 1959}}\n |birth_place         = [[Arras]]\n}}\n\n'''Sophie Malbranque''' (born 24 December 1959) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialised in the [[400 metres|400 meters]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nShe won three French 400m championship titles, two outdoor in 1980 and 1981, and one indoor in 1981.\n\nShe participated in the [[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1980 Olympics]] in Moscow, where she was eliminated in the heats of the 400m.\n\n===  prize list  ===\n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French Championships in Athletics]]   :  \n** 2 times winner of the 400m 1980 and 1981   \n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme en salle|French Athletics Indoor Championships]]   :  \n** winner of the 400 m in 1981\n\n=== Records ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''Personal records'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n|-\n|400 m\n|51 s 81\n|\n|1980\n|}\n\n==References ==\n{{Empty section|date=February 2016}}\n\n==  External links  ==\n*  Docathl\u00e92003, French Athletics Federation, 2003 p.&nbsp;398   \n*   <span class=\"indicateur-langue\">(<abbr class=\"abbr\" title=\"Langue : anglais\">in</abbr>)</span><span> Olympic profile</span><nowiki>   </nowiki>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ma/sophie-malbranque-1.html Sophie Malbranque]<span> on </span>''sports-reference.com''\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Malbranque, Sophie}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:French female sprinters]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of France]]\n[[Category:Universiade meda