{"title_page": "Fran\u00e7oise Leroux", "text_new": "{{Infobox Athlete\n |name                       = Fran\u00e7oise Leroux\n |event                = [[:fr:Sprint (athl\u00e9tisme)|Sprint]]\n |nationality               = {{FRA}}\n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age| 4 October 1961}}\n |birth_place         = [[Limoges]]\n |height                    = 1.60m\n |regionals  = [[:fr:Championnats d'Europe d'athl\u00e9tisme|European Championships]]\n|regionals 2 = [[:fr:Championnats d'Europe d'athl\u00e9tisme en salle|European Indoor Championships]]\n}}\n\n'''Fran\u00e7oise Leroux''', born '''Philippe''' on 4 October 1961 at [[Limoges]], is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialised in the [[Sprint (running)|sprint]]<nowiki/>s, and who ran for club CA Marignane SA. She competed in the [[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 100 metres|women's 100 metres]] at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/le/francoise-leroux-1.html |title=Fran\u00e7oise Leroux Olympic Results |accessdate=6 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==  Prize list  ==\n\n=== International ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%; margin-bottom: 10px;\"\n|+'''International Awards'''\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Competition\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n|-\n|1986\n|[[1986 European Athletics Championships|European Championships]] \n|[[Stuttgart]]\n| align=\"center\" | 4th\n|4 \u00d7 100 m\n|-\n|1987\n|[[1987 World Championships in Athletics|World Championships]] \n|[[Rome]]\n| align=\"center\" | 8th\n|4 \u00d7 100 m\n|-\n|1988\n|[[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]\n|[[Seoul]]\n| align=\"center\" | 7th\n|4 \u00d7 100 m\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1989\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Jeux de la Francophonie|Games of La Francophonie]] \n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Casablanca]]\n| align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"gold\" | 1st\n|4 \u00d7 100 m\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 5th\n|100 m\n\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==  External links  ==\n* {{IAAF name|id = 61080}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leroux, Francoise}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:French female sprinters]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of France]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Athlete\n |name                       = Fran\u00e7oise Leroux\n |event                = [[:fr:Sprint (athl\u00e9tisme)|Sprint]]\n |nationality               = {{FRA}}\n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age| 4 October 1961}}\n |birth_place         = [[Limoges]]\n |height                    = 1.60m\n |regionals  = [[:fr:Championnats d'Europe d'athl\u00e9tisme|European Championships]]\n|regionals 2 = [[:fr:Championnats d'Europe d'athl\u00e9tisme en salle|European Indoor Championships]]\n}}\n\n'''Fran\u00e7oise Leroux''', born '''Philippe''' on 4 October 1961 at [[Limoges]], is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialised in the [[Sprint (running)|sprint]]<nowiki/>s, and who ran for club CA Marignane SA. She competed in the [[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 100 metres|women's 100 metres]] at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/le/francoise-leroux-1.html |title=Fran\u00e7oise Leroux Olympic Results |accessdate=6 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==  Prize list  ==\n\n=== International ===\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%; margin-bottom: 10px;\"\n|+'''International Awards'''\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Competition\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n|-\n|1986\n|[[1986 European Athletics Championships|European Champ