{"title_page": "Muriel Linsolas", "text_new": "{{Infobox Athlete\n | name                        = Muriel Linsolas\n | event                 = [[distance running]]\n | nationality                = [[France|French]]\n | birth_date          = {{birth-date and age |24 September 1965}}\n | birth_place          = [[Avignon]]\n}}\n\n'''Muriel Linsolas''' (born September 24, 1965 at [[Avignon]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialized in the [[Long-distance running|distance races]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nShe won the French national title in the [[10,000 metres|10,000 meters]] in 1998 and the [[Half marathon|half-marathon]] in 1996 and 1997.\n\nIn 1996, during the [[1996 IAAF World Half Marathon Championships|IAAF World Half Marathon Championships]] at [[Palma, Majorca|Palma]], Spain, she won the silver medal in the team event alongside her compatriots [[Zahia Dahmani]] and [[:fr:Christine Mallo|Christine Mallo]].\n\n=== Prize list  ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''International Awards'''\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Competition\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" | Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n|-\n|1996\n|[[1996 IAAF World Half Marathon Championships|Half Marathon World Championships]] \n|[[Palma, Majorca|Palma]]\n| align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"silver\" | 2nd\n|Team\n|3:38:44\n|}\n\n=== Records ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''Personal Bests'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n|-\n|[[10,000 metres|10 000 m]]\n|32:57.83\n|\n|1998\n|-\n|[[Half marathon|Half-marathon]]\n|1:13:33\n|\n|1996\n|-\n|[[Marathon]]\n|2:36:54\n|\n|1996\n|}\n\n==Notes and references==\n\n{{Empty section|date=April 2016}}\n\n== Sources ==\n* DocAthl\u00e9 2003 - F\u00e9d\u00e9ration fran\u00e7aise d'athl\u00e9tisme - p.&nbsp;417\n\n== External links  ==\n* {{IAAF name|id=131065}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Linsolas, Muriel}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French female long-distance runners]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Avignon]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Athlete\n | name                        = Muriel Linsolas\n | event                 = [[distance running]]\n | nationality                = [[France|French]]\n | birth_date          = {{birth-date and age |24 September 1965}}\n | birth_place          = [[Avignon]]\n}}\n\n'''Muriel Linsolas''' (born September 24, 1965 at [[Avignon]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialized in the [[Long-distance running|distance races]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nShe won the French national title in the [[10,000 metres|10,000 meters]] in 1998 and the [[Half marathon|half-marathon]] in 1996 and 1997.\n\nIn 1996, during the [[1996 IAAF World Half Marathon Championships|IAAF World Half Marathon Championships]] at [[Palma, Majorca|Palma]], Spain, she won the silver medal in the team event alongside her compatriots [[Zahia Dahmani]] and [[:fr:Christine Mallo|Christine Mallo]].\n\n=== Prize list  ===\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''International Awards'''\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Competition\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" | Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n|-\n|1996\n|[[1996 IAAF World Half Marathon Championships|Half Marathon World Championships]] \n|[[Palma, Majorca|Palma]]\n| align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"silver\" | 2nd\n|Team\n|3:38:44\n|}\n\n=== Records ===\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''Personal Bests'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\