{"title_page": "Caroline Honor\u00e9", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox Athlete\n |nom                       = Caroline Honor\u00e9\n |event                = [[Triple Jump]]\n |years_active            = 1990s\n |nationality               = {{FRA}} \n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age |29 April 1970}}\n |birth_place         = [[Clermont-Ferrand]]\n}}\n'''Caroline Honor\u00e9''' (born [[:fr:29 avril en sport|29 April]] [[1970 in sports|1970]] at [[Clermont-Ferrand]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialized in the [[triple jump]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nShe won two titles [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French National Championships]] in the [[triple jump]]: in 1993 and 1996.\n\nShe twice improved the [[:fr:Record de France du triple saut|French triple jump record]]:  13.51 m and 13.65 m, done  on 23 July 1993  at [[Annecy]] during the [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1993|French championships]].\n\n=== Prize list  ===\n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French Championships in Athletics]]   :  \n** winner of the triple jump [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1993|1993]] and [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1996|1996]]\n\n=== Records ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''Personal records'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n|-\n|Triple jump\n|13.84 m\n|\n|1999\n|}\n\n== Notes and references  ==\n* Docathl\u00e92003, F\u00e9d\u00e9ration fran\u00e7aise d'athl\u00e9tisme, 2003, p.&nbsp;409\n\n== External links  ==\n* {{IAAF name|id=68178}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Honore, Caroline}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French female triple jumpers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Clermont-Ferrand]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox Athlete\n |nom                       = Caroline Honor\u00e9\n |event                = [[Triple Jump]]\n |years_active            = 1990s\n |nationality               = {{FRA}} \n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age |29 April 1970}}\n |birth_place         = [[Clermont-Ferrand]]\n}}\n'''Caroline Honor\u00e9''' (born [[:fr:29 avril en sport|29 April]] [[1970 in sports|1970]] at [[Clermont-Ferrand]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialized in the [[triple jump]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nShe won two titles [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French National Championships]] in the [[triple jump]]: in 1993 and 1996.\n\nShe twice improved the [[:fr:Record de France du triple saut|French triple jump record]]:  13.51 m and 13.65 m, done  on 23 July 1993  at [[Annecy]] during the [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1993|French championships]].\n\n=== Prize list  ===\n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French Championships in Athletics]]   :  \n** winner of the triple jump [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1993|1993]] and [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 1996|1996]]\n\n=== Records ===\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''Personal records'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n|-\n|Triple jump\n|13.84 m\n|\n|1999\n|}\n\n== Notes and references  ==\n* Docathl\u00e92003, F\u00e9d\u00e9ration fran\u00e7aise d'athl\u00e9tisme, 2003, p.&nbsp;409\n\n== External links  ==\n* {{IAAF name|id=68178}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Honore, Caroline}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French female triple jumpers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Clermont-Ferrand]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "WOSlinker", "label": "safe", "comment": "tidy wikitable option