{"title_page": "Vanessa Gladone", "text_new": "{{short description|French athlete}}\n{{Infobox Athlete\n |name                       = Vanessa Gladone\n |event                = [[Triple Jump]], [[Long Jump]]\n |nationality               = {{FRA}} \n |birth_date         = {{birth-date and age |3 June 1982}}\n |birth_place         = [[Sch\u0153lcher]]\n}}\n\n'''Vanessa Gladone''' (born [[:fr:3 juin en sport|June 3]]   [[1982 in sports|1982]] at [[Sch\u0153lcher]]) is a former French [[Sport of athletics|athlete]], who specialized in the [[triple jump]] and [[Long jump]].\n\n==  Biography  ==\nIn 2009, she won [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French national championships]] in the [[triple jump]] and [[Long jump]].\n\nShe was also an accomplished [[High Jump]] athlete with a best of 1.83m in 2009\n<ref>[http://bases.athle.com/asp.net/athletes.aspx?base=biographies&seq=504947524455514847524752 Vanessa Gladone] Retrieved on\n19-03-2016</ref>\nand her best performance in the  [[Heptathlon]] was 5622 points<ref>[http://www.athle.fr/asp.net/main.news/news.aspx?newsid=7896] Retrieved on 19-03-2016</ref>\n\nRetired from track since 2012, she  now hosts on TV.\n\n===  prize list  ===\n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme|French Championships in Athletics]]   :  \n** winner of the triple jump [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 2009|2009]]   \n** winner of the long jump [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme 2009|2009]]   \n* [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme en salle|French Indoors Athletics Championships]]:  \n** winner of the long jump [[:fr:Championnats de France d'athl\u00e9tisme en salle 2010|2010]]\n\n=== Records ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+'''personal records'''\n\n! scope=\"col\" |Event\n! scope=\"col\" | Performance\n! scope=\"col\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n|-\n|[[Long jump]]\n|6.59 m\n|[[Reims]]\n|July 14, 2009\n|-\n|[[Triple jump]]\n|14.13 m\n